                    <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                        <ab>
                          <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" key="Apollo Pytios">Ἀπόλλων<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied>
                          <lb n="2"/>Πυτίωι</persName>
                          <lb n="3"/><rs type="institution" subtype="official" role="builder" key="hiereus" ref="#itanos"><w lemma="ἱερατεύω">ἱερατεύσας</w>
                          <lb n="3a"/><space quantity="1" unit="line"/>
                          <lb n="4"/><persName type="attested" key="Pheidon f. Pheidon"><name nymRef="Φείδων">Φείδων</name>
                          <lb n="5"/><name nymRef="Φείδων" type="patronymic">Φείδωνος</name></persName></rs>
                          <lb n="6"/>καὶ Ἱαρὼι
                          <lb n="7"/>Σωναύτα
                          <lb n="8"/>τὸ <w lemma="ἀνδριάντιον">ἀνδριάν<lb 
                        break="no" n="9"/>τιον</w> καὶ τὸν
                          <lb n="10"/><w lemma="χρύσεος">χρύσεον</w>
                          <lb n="11"/><w lemma="στέφανος">στέφανο<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></w>
                          <lb n="12"/>τὸν π<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                          <lb n="12a"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
                          </ab>
                    </div>
                    <div type="commentary">
                        <p>La dedica ad Apollo <foreign>Pytios</foreign>, relativa ad una statuetta e ad una corona d’oro, è posta dall’ex sacerdote Pheidon figlio di Pheidon e da una donna, Hiaro figlia di Sonautas.</p>
                <p><emph>Elementi istituzionali o altri termini rilevanti</emph>: <ref type="inst" target="#hiereus"><foreign>hiereus</foreign></ref>.</p>
